The paper deals with classifying web and other PoC exploits for publicly disclosed software vulnerabilities, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of text mining and topic modeling to enhance software vulnerability information suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential for semi-automatic classification of exploits in existing tracking infrastructures, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and database systems (cs.DB).
